03:53.885 --> 03:58.760
[ Dog barking in distance ]

03:58.803 --> 04:02.329
Bill? Bill!
Dear God.

04:02.372 --> 04:07.377
Bill?
-[ Groaning ]

04:07.421 --> 04:11.425
Jesus Christ.

04:11.468 --> 04:16.299
[ Both grunting ]

04:16.343 --> 04:19.128
What -- What happened?

04:19.171 --> 04:20.869
He was here
when I got home.

04:20.912 --> 04:23.088
Well, do you know him?

04:23.132 --> 04:26.091
He was inside the house.

04:26.135 --> 04:27.876
He had a gun.

04:27.919 --> 04:29.965
It's --
it's here someplace.

04:30.008 --> 04:32.315
Well, don't worry.
I'll find it, I'll find it.

04:32.359 --> 04:34.404
I didn't just shoot him
for no reason.

04:34.448 --> 04:36.014
But of course not!
I saw it!

04:36.058 --> 04:37.973
I saw the whole fight.
He was gonna kill you!

04:38.016 --> 04:39.670
I will testify to that, Bill.

04:39.714 --> 04:42.804
He was in my house.

04:42.847 --> 04:43.674
Holly.

04:43.718 --> 04:45.502
No, she's not here.

04:45.546 --> 04:47.678
Bill.
Bill, listen to me.

04:47.722 --> 04:49.550
I just saw her drive off
20 minutes ago.

04:49.593 --> 04:52.030
She is not here.

04:52.074 --> 04:54.337
Jesus Christ.
Come here, sit down.

04:54.381 --> 04:57.601
Here.
I beg you.

04:57.645 --> 04:59.255
[ Groaning ]

04:59.299 --> 05:03.041
Oh. Jesus.

05:03.085 --> 05:05.696
Here, can you
just give me that?

05:05.740 --> 05:08.743
Ow. It's evidence now.

05:08.786 --> 05:11.963
Seeing fucking stars
and comets and ev--

05:12.007 --> 05:14.357
You probably have a c--
probably have a concussion.

05:14.401 --> 05:15.489
[ Door opens ]

05:15.532 --> 05:16.446
Jesus Christ.

05:16.490 --> 05:17.621
Well, if I don't,

05:17.665 --> 05:18.927
it's doing a bloody
imitation of one.

05:20.450 --> 05:23.366
Elliot: Oh, my God!
What the hell happened?

05:23.410 --> 05:28.458
Al...Something --
He works in the hospital.

05:28.502 --> 05:30.852
He killed a dog.

05:30.895 --> 05:33.898
Ah -- I think
I just might puke.

05:33.942 --> 05:35.378
Okay. Elliot, could you
get some water or something?

05:35.422 --> 05:37.119
-Sure.
-Uh, it's through there

05:37.162 --> 05:38.381
in the kitchen,
and call 911.

05:38.425 --> 05:42.342
-Okay.
-Also -- like a damp towel.

05:42.385 --> 05:44.387
Where else
are you hurt?

05:44.431 --> 05:49.697
Uh, my ribs, eh, shoulders,
knee, elbow, balls.

05:49.740 --> 05:51.481
Yeah, well, they're
certainly big enough --

05:51.525 --> 05:52.917
pretty hard to miss, yeah?

05:52.961 --> 05:54.397
-Ugh.
-They're --

05:54.441 --> 05:55.398
they're on their way.
Somebody already called them.

05:55.442 --> 05:57.531
Here.
Please.

05:57.574 --> 06:00.229
-Put this on his head.
-Yeah, thank you.

06:00.272 --> 06:04.364
All right. I'm gonna
wait outside for them.

06:04.407 --> 06:06.235
Let me just staunch this.
Hold on a minute.

06:06.278 --> 06:07.497
He called me Kermit.

06:07.541 --> 06:09.151
What?

06:09.194 --> 06:15.070
He called me Kermit.

06:15.113 --> 06:17.768
[ Siren wailing,
dog barking in distance ]

06:17.812 --> 06:21.555
But h-h-how
is that possible?

06:21.598 --> 06:23.165
I don't know.

06:23.208 --> 06:25.385
Here, hold still.

06:25.428 --> 06:27.517
[ Breathing heavily ]

06:27.561 --> 06:29.867
[ Siren wailing ]

06:38.702 --> 06:41.401
[ Fire crackling ]

06:41.444 --> 06:50.497
♪♪

06:50.540 --> 06:53.282
[ Sighs ]

06:53.325 --> 06:59.419
♪♪

06:59.462 --> 07:05.555
♪♪

07:05.599 --> 07:11.474
♪♪

07:11.518 --> 07:17.611
♪♪

07:17.654 --> 07:23.747
♪♪

07:23.791 --> 07:29.884
♪♪

07:29.927 --> 07:36.020
♪♪

07:36.064 --> 07:38.196
[ Switch clicks ]

07:38.240 --> 07:39.720
Marco.

07:39.763 --> 07:42.244
Polo.

07:42.287 --> 07:43.463
Hi, brother.

07:43.506 --> 07:45.552
[ Chuckles ]

07:45.595 --> 07:52.384
♪♪

07:52.428 --> 07:53.690
Is Mom here?

07:53.734 --> 07:58.086
I told you --
She's gone.

07:58.129 --> 07:59.870
Can we watch TV?

07:59.914 --> 08:04.832
[ Chuckles ]
Of course we can.

08:04.875 --> 08:07.791
[ Switch clicks ]

08:07.835 --> 08:09.358
When did they start?

08:09.401 --> 08:11.229
8:58.

08:11.273 --> 08:14.102
I've never seen
brain activity this strong.

08:14.145 --> 08:15.495
These are the readings
of someone

08:15.538 --> 08:17.453
who stepped on
a third rail.

08:26.593 --> 08:28.508
Gotcha.

08:28.551 --> 08:30.205
[ Monitors beeping ]

08:35.906 --> 08:38.561
You can't hide anymore, asshole.

08:38.605 --> 08:40.650
Your public awaits.

08:40.694 --> 08:42.347
[ Door closes,
police radio chatter ]

08:42.391 --> 08:44.698
[ Indistinct conversations ]

08:44.741 --> 08:48.571
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

08:48.615 --> 08:51.356
So, will I live?

08:51.400 --> 08:53.576
I don't like your vitals,
to be honest with you.

08:53.620 --> 08:56.318
You're showing signs
of post-concussive trauma.

08:56.361 --> 08:58.668
You're a cheery fuck.

08:58.712 --> 08:59.974
That's the personality
type you want

09:00.017 --> 09:01.889
in your paramedic,
fucking Carrot Top?

09:01.932 --> 09:04.195
What the fuck
is Carrot Top?

09:04.239 --> 09:05.980
Two rounds, huh?

09:06.023 --> 09:08.243
Ah, he kept coming.

09:08.286 --> 09:11.072
He's big, but, uh...

09:11.115 --> 09:12.987
He wouldn't stop.

09:13.030 --> 09:14.989
I'm not judging,
I'm just saying

09:15.032 --> 09:16.904
if you'd gone for
that headshot first,

09:16.947 --> 09:17.948
you could've saved
a bullet.

09:17.992 --> 09:19.689
Oh, fuck off.

09:19.733 --> 09:23.214
I'll be back.

09:23.258 --> 09:26.043
Uh, the phone --
the phone picked up,

09:26.087 --> 09:29.133
and I heard someone scream
"I'm gonna" --

09:29.177 --> 09:32.397
"I'm gonna
fuck you up, Kermit,"

09:32.441 --> 09:36.663
and, um, uh, then --
then there was --

09:36.706 --> 09:38.490
And when you approached
the house,

09:38.534 --> 09:40.884
that's when you saw
the deceased attempting to...?

09:40.928 --> 09:43.234
Well,
Bill was on the floor.

09:43.278 --> 09:44.888
He had him on the floor,
he pinned him down,

09:44.932 --> 09:47.195
he was on his back,
and the guy was just

09:47.238 --> 09:50.241
pounding and punching
and punching his face.

09:50.285 --> 09:52.635
I th-- thought he was
gonna kill him.

09:52.679 --> 09:57.248
[ Indistinct conversations ]

09:57.292 --> 09:59.033
-Okay.
-[ Groans ]

09:59.076 --> 10:01.470
Your statements
all jibe.

10:01.513 --> 10:03.603
Your ex-wife heard
the whole thing on the phone.

10:03.646 --> 10:04.604
Did you know that?

10:04.647 --> 10:06.170
No, I didn't.

10:06.214 --> 10:08.695
She's the one
that called 911.

10:08.738 --> 10:11.698
Good news is it's all
cut and dry --

10:11.741 --> 10:13.700
got out of jail,
took the gun he stole,

10:13.743 --> 10:16.485
and came looking for you.

10:16.528 --> 10:17.921
Yeah.

10:17.965 --> 10:22.491
It all checks out
except the "why" of it all.

10:22.534 --> 10:24.362
Did you talk to
to the brother yet?

10:24.406 --> 10:27.104
Just sent a unit
over there.

10:27.148 --> 10:30.064
I'll catch up with you
at the hospital.

10:30.107 --> 10:32.849
On three.
One, two, three.

10:32.893 --> 10:33.981
Hey, wait, wait.
What?

10:34.024 --> 10:36.157
-Careful.
-What's happening?

10:36.200 --> 10:39.334
Okay, okay. We're gonna
go to the hospital.

10:39.377 --> 10:40.683
I don't really need to
go to the hospital.

10:40.727 --> 10:42.859
You need a hospital,
m' man, trust me.

10:42.903 --> 10:46.123
[ Groans ]

10:46.167 --> 10:48.125
Gentle, gentle.

10:48.169 --> 10:49.910
[ Police radio chatter ]

10:49.953 --> 10:52.434
[ Gurney clanks ]

10:52.477 --> 10:55.698
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:55.742 --> 10:58.570
[ Insects chirping,
dog barking in distance ]

11:07.754 --> 11:09.799
[ Cellphone ringing ]

11:15.718 --> 11:18.982
Hi, Ida.

11:19.026 --> 11:21.593
Jerome,
I'm ready to go.

11:21.637 --> 11:22.725
Jerome.

11:22.769 --> 11:24.771
Jerome!

11:24.814 --> 11:26.337
Can you turn off
your fucking music for,

11:26.381 --> 11:27.730
like, one second?What the hell?

11:27.774 --> 11:29.079
I need a ride to Grace's.
You promised.

11:29.123 --> 11:30.907
Whoa, whoa, what is with
your attitude lately?

11:30.951 --> 11:32.256
-Attitude?
-Yes. Attitude.

11:32.300 --> 11:34.128
You've been stressing
everybody out -- Pops, me --

11:34.171 --> 11:34.998
I've been walking
around like --

11:35.042 --> 11:36.217
I'm stressing Dad out?

11:36.260 --> 11:37.435
My allowance
has been cut in half,

11:37.479 --> 11:38.523
we stopped eating out,

11:38.567 --> 11:39.829
and he just got rid of cable

11:39.873 --> 11:41.396
because we can't afford it.

11:41.439 --> 11:43.050
So before you get up
all in my face,

11:43.093 --> 11:45.443
look in the mirror,
Harvard.

11:45.487 --> 11:49.230
♪♪

11:49.273 --> 11:50.710
Don't you need a ride?

11:50.753 --> 11:53.190
I can -- I can drive you.

11:53.234 --> 11:55.192
I'll walk.

11:55.236 --> 11:58.369
[ Insects chirping,
door closes ]

12:01.851 --> 12:03.244
[ Keys clatter ]

12:03.287 --> 12:04.245
[ Sighs ]

12:04.288 --> 12:07.074
[ Dog whines, panting ]

12:41.978 --> 12:44.241
[ Sighs ]

12:52.946 --> 12:56.123
[ Cellphone ringing ]

13:03.434 --> 13:05.393
Hey. Ida?

13:05.436 --> 13:10.572
Yeah.

13:10.615 --> 13:13.488
Wh-- Yes.

13:13.531 --> 13:14.968
Yeah, yeah. I'll be there --
I'll be there in a minute, okay?

13:15.011 --> 13:17.057
Okay.

13:25.717 --> 13:26.980
-Ida!
-Hi.

13:27.023 --> 13:28.677
-Hey.
-Hey, how's he doing?

13:28.720 --> 13:29.852
Oh, Jesus --
I-I don't know.

13:29.896 --> 13:31.811
He took a hell of a beating.

13:31.854 --> 13:32.986
I don't know how he's doing now.

13:33.029 --> 13:34.639
-Okay.
-What?

13:34.683 --> 13:35.858
-Hey.
-Hey.

13:35.902 --> 13:38.339
-Hi.
-Uh, well, he, uh, he --

13:38.382 --> 13:40.515
he has a concussion
and, uh, some --

13:40.558 --> 13:44.301
some torn ligaments, um,
uh, cracked ribs,

13:44.345 --> 13:46.216
which are, uh, are --
are gonna hurt like hell,

13:46.260 --> 13:48.349
but he's okay.

13:48.392 --> 13:52.527
-Oh.
-Uh, he's alive.

13:52.570 --> 13:54.964
-Wow. Wow.
-Okay, good. See?

13:55.008 --> 13:57.053
Everything's fine, all right?

13:57.097 --> 13:58.489
When can we see him?

13:58.533 --> 14:00.013
They're not letting anybody
back there.

14:00.056 --> 14:02.754
Belive me, I tried.

14:02.798 --> 14:04.887
Okay,
so what happened?

14:04.931 --> 14:06.541
I don't know
who this guy was.

14:06.584 --> 14:09.500
It was just
an unbelievable fight.

14:09.544 --> 14:11.415
-Bill shot him.
-Shot him?

14:11.459 --> 14:13.896
Yeah, dead.

14:13.940 --> 14:19.423
[ Indistinct conversations ]

14:19.467 --> 14:20.860
Police are crawling
all over his house now.

14:20.903 --> 14:22.426
It's a bad scene.

14:22.470 --> 14:26.126
He cut up his brother,
slit his throat.

14:26.169 --> 14:30.957
It was grim, man -- looked like
some kind of van Gogh shit.

14:31.000 --> 14:32.828
You saw him
with his brother, right?

14:32.872 --> 14:34.569
Make any sense to you?

14:34.612 --> 14:38.268
I know, but it's --
it's a slam dunk.

14:38.312 --> 14:39.661
He slashes his brother
to death,

14:39.704 --> 14:42.751
and he comes at you
with my gun.

14:42.794 --> 14:44.231
Did -- Did they
get the gun?

14:44.274 --> 14:46.755
I -- We got it, and it's
bagged for evidence.

14:46.798 --> 14:50.150
Don't worry about it.

14:50.193 --> 14:53.153
The Al Jursak I talked
to wasn't the same guy

14:53.196 --> 14:56.765
I killed --
not the same guy.

14:56.808 --> 14:58.680
[ Grunts ]

14:58.723 --> 15:00.334
He told me in the street
that he had lap--

15:00.377 --> 15:03.903
lapses of memory and stuff.

15:03.946 --> 15:08.516
But just before
the second shot,

15:08.559 --> 15:11.562
my -- he gave me this look
like it was as if he didn't --

15:11.606 --> 15:13.086
he didn't quite know
where he was...

15:13.129 --> 15:15.175
♪♪

15:15.218 --> 15:17.612
...like you were waking out
of a nightmare

15:17.655 --> 15:19.788
looking down
the barrel of a gun.

15:19.831 --> 15:22.791
And you gave him
a head tap anyway?

15:22.834 --> 15:24.880
It was a fraction
of a second

15:24.924 --> 15:26.316
as I was pulling the trigger,
but...

15:26.360 --> 15:29.319
But in the fraction
of a second?

15:29.363 --> 15:33.758
I think he was coming back
into his own mind.

15:33.802 --> 15:35.935
And who was he
before that?

15:35.978 --> 15:39.851
[ Monitors beeping ]

15:39.895 --> 15:44.856
Brady Hartsfield.

15:44.900 --> 15:47.381
We got to stop looking
for rational explanations

15:47.424 --> 15:49.992
for stuff that's --
they're unexplainable.

15:50.036 --> 15:54.997
I know what I saw.

15:55.041 --> 15:59.001
Just before I killed this guy,
he was Brady Hartsfield --

15:59.045 --> 16:01.264
Called me Kermit
for fuck's sake.

16:01.308 --> 16:05.094
Like...

16:05.138 --> 16:07.183
Whether you want to believe
it or not, people are dying

16:07.227 --> 16:11.666
'cause he's been kept alive
in this hospital.

16:11.709 --> 16:13.102
He is, he is.

16:13.146 --> 16:16.192
He's is. He's breathing
up in his room.

16:16.236 --> 16:18.194
[ Sighs ]

16:18.238 --> 16:20.544
And he's looking out
for the next --

16:20.588 --> 16:24.679
He's looking for the next
Library Al, the next Sadie.

16:24.722 --> 16:27.812
Are we gonna just
gonna let it go on

16:27.856 --> 16:30.424
'cause we don't want
to believe that it can?

16:30.467 --> 16:33.253
I want to make another run
at Pettimore.

16:33.296 --> 16:35.603
He's got two
dead employees now.

16:35.646 --> 16:37.909
Maybe he's ready to belive
that there is such a thing

16:37.953 --> 16:39.476
as bad publicity.

16:39.520 --> 16:43.437
Yeah. Thanks.

16:43.480 --> 16:46.744
You understand what we're
both thinking here is...?

16:46.788 --> 16:50.009
Categorically insane.

16:50.052 --> 16:52.837
Are we just gonna
let it go on?

16:52.881 --> 16:55.449
Fuck no.

16:55.492 --> 16:56.754
Get some rest.

16:56.798 --> 16:59.061
Thanks.

16:59.105 --> 17:01.194
[ Indistinct conversations ]

17:01.237 --> 17:05.676
[ Sighs ]

17:05.720 --> 17:08.679
Have you been here
the whole time?

17:08.723 --> 17:09.811
[ Chuckles ]

17:09.854 --> 17:12.335
[ Snorts, groans ]

17:12.379 --> 17:13.206
Should I --

17:13.249 --> 17:14.816
No,
don't make me laugh.

17:14.859 --> 17:15.773
-I'm sorry.
-It's all right.

17:15.817 --> 17:17.775
It's not your fault.

17:17.819 --> 17:22.171
[ Grunts ]

17:22.215 --> 17:24.869
Whoever, whatever
Brady Hartsfield is these days,

17:24.913 --> 17:27.872
he can't keep on
hurting people --

17:27.916 --> 17:31.137
You know,
not people I...

17:31.180 --> 17:34.096
He can't.
You know I won't allow it.

17:34.140 --> 17:37.143
If he is inhabiting people,
it's because of the medicine,

17:37.186 --> 17:38.709
you know, the drugs
that they're giving him,

17:38.753 --> 17:41.103
and we just have to prove
that they're giving him

17:41.147 --> 17:43.801
illegal drugs in order
for them to stop

17:43.845 --> 17:46.935
giving him illegal drugs.
[ Sniffles ]

17:46.978 --> 17:50.286
Yeah.

17:50.330 --> 17:52.462
That's right.

17:52.506 --> 17:56.684
It all goes away...

17:56.727 --> 18:01.297
This. Us.

18:01.341 --> 18:03.952
It all goes away.

18:03.995 --> 18:07.738
I mean, today you almost...

18:07.782 --> 18:09.392
I didn't.

18:09.436 --> 18:11.612
Yeah, could have, though.

18:11.655 --> 18:15.050
And I can't hold this world
sometimes.

18:15.094 --> 18:19.098
I can't -- 'cause I know
that it doesn't hold me.

18:19.141 --> 18:23.189
It's just...
letting me visit.

18:23.232 --> 18:27.976
Yeah.
We're renting for sure.

18:28.019 --> 18:30.805
[ Sniffling ]

18:30.848 --> 18:32.763
No option to buy.

18:32.807 --> 18:35.201
[ Snorts ]
Oh, sorry.

18:40.771 --> 18:44.688
I wish I could tell you...

18:44.732 --> 18:47.865
what you mean to me...

18:47.909 --> 18:50.129
[ Sniffling ]

18:50.172 --> 18:52.653
...and how much
that frightens me.

18:52.696 --> 18:55.960
[ Monitors beeping ]

18:56.004 --> 18:58.746
It cuts both ways.

18:58.789 --> 19:01.966
I --
I don't like the feeling.

19:02.010 --> 19:03.185
I know.

19:03.229 --> 19:06.188
[ Sighs ]

19:06.232 --> 19:10.323
Caring for people
is scary.

19:10.366 --> 19:12.934
Happiness is lovely.

19:12.977 --> 19:14.240
Mm-hmm.

19:14.283 --> 19:18.722
Not --
Not really controllable.

19:18.766 --> 19:20.768
You can't tie it
to a post.

19:20.811 --> 19:24.989
[ Sniffles ]

19:25.033 --> 19:27.818
Uh, um --

19:27.862 --> 19:29.820
Can't get rid
of you, can I?

19:29.864 --> 19:32.519
About to say the same thing.

19:32.562 --> 19:34.434
We're moving you
to a room upstairs.

19:34.477 --> 19:36.262
Okay.

19:36.305 --> 19:38.873
[ Monitors beeping ]

19:38.916 --> 19:44.487
[ Ventilator hissing ]

19:44.531 --> 19:45.836
Funny, I don't remember
giving the go-ahead

19:45.880 --> 19:47.360
on open brain surgery.

19:47.403 --> 19:50.014
It was an emergency procedure,
all right?

19:50.058 --> 19:51.973
Our deal was that I'd
protect you from Pettimore

19:52.016 --> 19:53.453
if you run everything
by me --

19:53.496 --> 19:54.932
If he gets an infection,
a blood clot,

19:54.976 --> 19:56.934
a fucking paper cut,
you run everything by me.

19:56.978 --> 19:59.023
I told you
it was an emergency.

19:59.067 --> 20:00.329
I'm telling Pettimore
to boot him to Crestmore

20:00.373 --> 20:02.636
as soon as possible.

20:02.679 --> 20:04.725
He moved his hands earlier.

20:04.768 --> 20:06.770
And he's been using
the eye-apparatus

20:06.814 --> 20:08.468
to type out messages.

20:08.511 --> 20:10.992
I mean, you -- you give me
one more month, a-and I swear,

20:11.035 --> 20:13.124
I'll get him
walking into court.

20:13.168 --> 20:14.822
We were supposed to be
partners in this,

20:14.865 --> 20:16.998
and then you fucking lied
to me over and over again.

20:17.041 --> 20:20.131
Now I'm done.

20:20.175 --> 20:22.438
Just one more push and --
and the floodgates will open.

20:22.482 --> 20:23.439
I swear.

20:23.483 --> 20:24.701
Two of your employees
are dead.

20:24.745 --> 20:26.225
But that has nothing
to do with him.

20:26.268 --> 20:26.790
No?

20:26.834 --> 20:30.968
No! I --

20:31.012 --> 20:33.623
The Germans, the Russians,
the Chinese --

20:33.667 --> 20:36.974
They're leagues ahead of us in
life-saving stem cell research,

20:37.018 --> 20:42.284
all because regulations
stymie progress in this country.

20:42.328 --> 20:43.633
If I have a chance
to -- to --

20:43.677 --> 20:46.593
to save lives, it's my
responsibility as a doctor,

20:46.636 --> 20:50.858
as a scientist,
to take on those risks.

20:50.901 --> 20:52.773
Maybe...

20:52.816 --> 20:54.775
but it ain't mine.

20:54.818 --> 20:57.125
Say your goodbyes.

20:57.168 --> 21:01.390
[ Indistinct conversations ]

21:01.434 --> 21:05.481
What the fuck, Bill?
They said you killed Al.

21:05.525 --> 21:07.396
He attacked me.

21:07.440 --> 21:10.269
He was armed.

21:10.312 --> 21:12.706
Two days ago,
he killed Montez's dog.

21:12.749 --> 21:13.794
God, it's crazy.

21:13.837 --> 21:17.406
Everyone here
is flipping out.

21:17.450 --> 21:20.453
Just give us a few to get him
set up in there, okay?

21:20.496 --> 21:22.498
Brian, can you
help me, please?

21:22.542 --> 21:26.197
Brian: Sure.

21:26.241 --> 21:30.463
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

21:30.506 --> 21:33.857
[ Indistinct conversations ]

21:33.901 --> 21:35.859
[ Door closes ]

21:35.903 --> 21:38.993
[ Ringing continues ]

21:42.213 --> 21:44.433
We're waiting for
our friend, Will.

21:44.477 --> 21:45.391
Hiya, friend.

21:45.434 --> 21:48.568
[ Knocking, dog whining ]

21:48.611 --> 21:50.221
-Sounds like a dog to me.
-Hi, Willie.

21:50.265 --> 21:52.659
How are you this morning?
Very good.

21:52.702 --> 21:55.618
I have a little surprise.
Close your eyes.

21:55.662 --> 21:56.358
All right, open up.

21:56.402 --> 21:59.230
I'm sick of apples.

21:59.274 --> 22:02.625
-Yeah.
-All right.

22:02.669 --> 22:05.672
That's Willie Whistle.

22:05.715 --> 22:08.196
I'm sick of this show.

22:08.239 --> 22:10.285
♪♪

22:10.329 --> 22:12.505
[ Clicking ]

22:12.548 --> 22:15.203
Maggie: The pain killers
will kick in pretty soon

22:15.246 --> 22:17.205
so you'll get
a good night's rest.

22:17.248 --> 22:19.163
We'll run a couple tests in
the morning and kick you loose.

22:19.207 --> 22:21.383
-Thanks, Maggie.
-Okay.

22:21.427 --> 22:23.951
Visiting hours are
almost over, folks.

22:23.994 --> 22:26.693
If you need anything,
tell them to beep me.

22:26.736 --> 22:28.085
I'm working a double.

22:28.129 --> 22:30.436
Okay, thanks, Maggie.

22:50.064 --> 22:53.328
Uh...

22:53.372 --> 22:57.376
time for you all to
shove off, I think.

22:57.419 --> 22:59.595
Um, I kind of feel
like sticking around.

22:59.639 --> 23:00.640
Yeah, me too.

23:00.683 --> 23:02.424
I'll stay for
a little bit longer

23:02.468 --> 23:07.386
as well, yeah.

23:07.429 --> 23:12.434
Can a man not convalesce
in peace, no?

23:12.478 --> 23:16.525
Oh, well, okay --
fair enough point.

23:16.569 --> 23:18.309
I'm just gonna be
down the hall.

23:18.353 --> 23:21.269
-Go home -- all of ya.
-Yes, Bill.

23:21.312 --> 23:22.662
You gonna eat
this apple sauce?

23:22.705 --> 23:24.707
-Choke on it.
-All right. Okay.

23:24.751 --> 23:26.405
Okay, remember that
the number-one killer

23:26.448 --> 23:28.972
of hospital patients
is staph infection, okay?

23:29.016 --> 23:31.105
So don't get one of those.

23:31.148 --> 23:33.890
Jesus.
How do I avoid that?

23:33.934 --> 23:36.284
Um, wash hands often, uh,

23:36.327 --> 23:38.939
keep cuts and scrapes
clean and bandaged,

23:38.982 --> 23:42.246
and, um, don't take any personal
items from other patients --

23:42.290 --> 23:43.422
especially those with, um,

23:43.465 --> 23:45.815
open wounds and
hacking coughs, okay?

23:45.859 --> 23:48.775
-Bye.
-[ Sighs ]

23:48.818 --> 23:51.517
Ah, pfft.

23:51.560 --> 23:55.434
[ Sighs ]

24:06.488 --> 24:08.359
[ Sighs ]

24:22.286 --> 24:27.509
Rest, okay?

24:27.553 --> 24:29.685
I'll be back
in a little bit.

24:29.729 --> 24:33.559
I will.

24:33.602 --> 24:36.475
[ Sighs ]

24:41.741 --> 24:44.526
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

24:44.570 --> 24:47.050
[ Indistinct conversations ]

25:05.416 --> 25:07.593
Donna: Come on!

25:07.636 --> 25:09.290
Ah -- damn it!

25:09.333 --> 25:11.510
Donna!
Donna!

25:11.553 --> 25:13.076
Donna.

25:13.120 --> 25:16.645
Hey.

25:16.689 --> 25:21.171
Hey. Hey.

25:21.215 --> 25:22.521
It's okay.

25:22.564 --> 25:25.262
[ Sighs ]

25:25.306 --> 25:28.657
[ Indistinct conversations ]

25:28.701 --> 25:32.182
When does it end, huh?

25:32.226 --> 25:35.577
When he's dead.

25:35.621 --> 25:37.884
And he killed a man.

25:37.927 --> 25:40.800
Nobody seems to give a shit
about that.

25:40.843 --> 25:42.323
Only to save his own life.

25:42.366 --> 25:44.325
I know.
I know.

25:44.368 --> 25:46.936
Of course I know that.

25:46.980 --> 25:52.594
[ Breathes deeply ]

25:52.638 --> 25:54.161
I hate this.

25:54.204 --> 25:56.119
Mm-hmm.

25:56.163 --> 25:57.643
I've never been good
at all this...

25:57.686 --> 25:59.079
Yeah.

25:59.122 --> 26:02.561
...mess.

26:02.604 --> 26:04.606
Well, girl,

26:04.650 --> 26:09.611
this is the guy
you married.

26:09.655 --> 26:12.353
This is who he is.

26:12.396 --> 26:14.485
[ Sighs ]

26:14.529 --> 26:17.271
[ Ringing continues ]

26:17.314 --> 26:20.491
[ Inhales deeply ]

26:20.535 --> 26:22.537
Oh, God.

26:22.581 --> 26:25.975
[ Mutters ]

26:26.019 --> 26:27.673
What did you want to eat?

26:27.716 --> 26:31.154
I don't care.
I don't --

26:31.198 --> 26:33.592
Anythi-- Pretzels.
Pretzels.

26:33.635 --> 26:36.725
Whatever.

26:36.769 --> 26:39.032
[ Pretzels thud ]

26:39.075 --> 26:43.079
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

26:51.174 --> 26:54.003
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

27:00.706 --> 27:04.710
Hey, Jerome.

27:04.753 --> 27:07.669
Where the hell is Holly?

27:07.713 --> 27:10.106
I don't know.

27:10.150 --> 27:12.543
Oh, for Christ's sake.

27:12.587 --> 27:13.675
[ Groans ]

27:13.719 --> 27:14.371
[ Grunts ]

27:14.415 --> 27:17.461
[ Monitors beeping ]

27:17.505 --> 27:20.551
[ Ventilator hissing ]

27:20.595 --> 27:26.688
♪♪

27:26.732 --> 27:32.999
♪♪

27:33.042 --> 27:39.396
♪♪

27:39.440 --> 27:45.707
♪♪

27:45.751 --> 27:47.230
You don't get to win.

27:47.274 --> 27:49.493
[ Tape rips ]

27:49.537 --> 27:53.889
♪♪

27:53.933 --> 27:56.936
[ Tape ripping ]

27:56.979 --> 28:04.073
♪♪

28:04.117 --> 28:06.597
You do not.

28:06.641 --> 28:15.345
♪♪

28:15.389 --> 28:18.435
[ Door opens, closes ]

28:18.479 --> 28:26.487
[ Monitor beeping,
ventilator hissing ]

28:26.530 --> 28:28.881
What are we even calling
what happened yesterday?

28:28.924 --> 28:31.231
One of your employees went off
the beam, killed his brother,

28:31.274 --> 28:33.755
then attempted to kill the man
who helped stop Brady Hartsfield

28:33.799 --> 28:35.670
from blowing up 200 people
at Edmund Mills.

28:35.714 --> 28:36.932
Yes.

28:36.976 --> 28:39.239
We'll call it
"the madness."

28:39.282 --> 28:41.763
The madness, then.

28:41.807 --> 28:43.112
In light
of yesterday's madness,

28:43.156 --> 28:44.679
I'm comfortable
transferring this patient

28:44.723 --> 28:46.855
the hell out of here.

28:46.899 --> 28:50.772
I'll start the paperwork.

28:50.816 --> 28:53.688
I won't forget this.

28:53.732 --> 28:59.215
[ Indistinct conversations ]

28:59.259 --> 29:00.564
I should be getting
the Nobel,

29:00.608 --> 29:02.828
not shipping my patient off
to hospice.

29:02.871 --> 29:04.612
No.

29:04.655 --> 29:07.528
The higher-ups have called
a meeting in about five minutes.

29:07.571 --> 29:09.225
Why?

29:09.269 --> 29:10.792
To review the efficacy
of our endeavors

29:10.836 --> 29:13.795
and decide if significant
reevaluation is warranted.

29:13.839 --> 29:15.405
What language is that?

29:15.449 --> 29:17.494
If said reevaluation concludes
that our potential exposure

29:17.538 --> 29:19.322
is too great
or could become so,

29:19.366 --> 29:20.802
the project will be
placed in turnaround

29:20.846 --> 29:22.325
or enter a trial period
of disintegration.

29:22.369 --> 29:23.457
I just --
I don't understand you.

29:23.500 --> 29:25.894
Speaking fucking English.

29:25.938 --> 29:28.897
They're terminating
the project, Felix.

29:28.941 --> 29:31.073
What?

29:31.117 --> 29:32.161
Liang's concluded
that they have

29:32.205 --> 29:34.207
all the trial data
that they need

29:34.250 --> 29:36.078
and that it would be best
that any evidence

29:36.122 --> 29:38.602
of Cerebellin dies in Crestmore
with Hartsfield.

29:38.646 --> 29:41.127
Y-You already told him
he's being transferred?

29:41.170 --> 29:42.911
The good news is that
Jiànkang Ni

29:42.955 --> 29:46.306
can use all of our findings
to refine the cocktail

29:46.349 --> 29:47.960
and eliminate
the side-effects.

29:48.003 --> 29:50.223
-Oh.
-And, yes, I told them.

29:50.266 --> 29:52.312
What did you expect me
to do?

29:52.355 --> 29:55.141
Help me stop it, maybe?

29:55.184 --> 29:57.665
You don't think things
are a little volatile?

29:57.708 --> 30:00.755
So, what, we just -- we flush
Hartsfield down the toilet,

30:00.799 --> 30:03.540
wait for the perfect specimen
to come and sit in our laps?

30:03.584 --> 30:04.933
No.

30:04.977 --> 30:09.242
Felix, your part in this
is done.

30:09.285 --> 30:12.854
What the fuck are you
talking about?

30:12.898 --> 30:15.857
You're too unstable.

30:15.901 --> 30:18.381
I am not unstable.

30:18.425 --> 30:21.297
You threatened me.

30:21.341 --> 30:23.952
Oh, come on,
I didn't th-- threaten you.

30:23.996 --> 30:25.475
Yes.

30:25.519 --> 30:27.173
Yes, you did.

30:27.216 --> 30:29.392
You hold my passport
hostage?

30:29.436 --> 30:30.872
Fuck you.

30:30.916 --> 30:32.265
Do you hear me?

30:32.308 --> 30:35.790
Fuck...you.

30:35.834 --> 30:40.490
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

30:40.534 --> 30:44.712
You know, what happened to
making a name for ourselves,

30:44.755 --> 30:46.888
"leaving our mark
on the history of science,"

30:46.932 --> 30:49.848
"getting the fuck
out of Bridgton"?

30:49.891 --> 30:50.892
There were
two employee deaths

30:50.936 --> 30:53.503
on your ward
in less than a month --

30:53.547 --> 30:55.549
ex-cop, a prosecutor
sniffing around,

30:55.592 --> 30:58.769
and glacial progress --
that's what happened.

30:58.813 --> 31:02.251
As of now, the FDA has no idea
that any of this is happening,

31:02.295 --> 31:04.601
and Liang wants
to keep it that way --

31:04.645 --> 31:06.603
especially if he's gonna be
selling to American markets

31:06.647 --> 31:10.869
in a couple of years.

31:10.912 --> 31:12.305
And when that happens,

31:12.348 --> 31:15.003
well, no, we didn't
change the world,

31:15.047 --> 31:16.918
but we have stock options.

31:16.962 --> 31:18.485
[ Sighs ]
Jesus Christ.

31:18.528 --> 31:21.618
Cora, I'm not in this
for stock options.

31:21.662 --> 31:23.707
I don't think
you're hearing me --

31:23.751 --> 31:27.102
You're not in this
at all anymore.

31:27.146 --> 31:29.713
Um -- What about us?

31:29.757 --> 31:31.977
Uh...

31:32.020 --> 31:34.370
Honey,

31:34.414 --> 31:36.807
I'm in this
for the long haul.

31:36.851 --> 31:39.288
You know that.

31:39.332 --> 31:41.290
Besides,
where would I go?

31:41.334 --> 31:44.554
You have my passport.

31:44.598 --> 31:46.861
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

31:46.905 --> 31:49.603
[ Indistinct conversations ]

31:49.646 --> 31:52.954
Oh, shit.

31:57.828 --> 32:00.222
[ Ringing continues ]

32:09.275 --> 32:10.667
[ Dialing ]

32:10.711 --> 32:11.973
Donna: Wait, wait --
I'm gonna come around.

32:12.017 --> 32:15.672
-Wait a minute.
-Okay.

32:15.716 --> 32:17.196
-[ Grunts ]
-[ Sighs ]

32:17.239 --> 32:18.240
I said wait.
What are you doing?

32:18.284 --> 32:19.328
I'm all right --
okay, okay, okay.

32:19.372 --> 32:20.329
Okay, watch out,
watch out.

32:20.373 --> 32:23.071
I got it, I got it,
I got it.

32:23.115 --> 32:25.378
Okay, easy.

32:25.421 --> 32:27.946
-You okay? Can you walk?
-Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

32:27.989 --> 32:29.469
Just a bit wobbly.

32:29.512 --> 32:32.037
All right. Here.
Here. Easy.

32:32.080 --> 32:35.040
-Lock the car, will you?
-Yep.

32:35.083 --> 32:36.650
[ Car alarm honks ]

32:36.693 --> 32:39.566
They said I'd be good
as new in a few days.

32:39.609 --> 32:41.046
Yeah?

32:41.089 --> 32:42.830
Yeah, like --
like it never happened.

32:42.873 --> 32:45.789
-Go ahead, get the door.
-Okay. All right, I got it.

32:45.833 --> 32:48.183
Just get the door.

32:48.227 --> 32:50.229
[ Birds chirping,
lock disengages ]

32:59.890 --> 33:02.589
[ Keys jingle, thud ]

33:02.632 --> 33:06.897
[ Sighs ]

33:06.941 --> 33:09.639
What's this?

33:09.683 --> 33:11.511
Home for lunch?

33:11.554 --> 33:13.730
No work today.

33:13.774 --> 33:15.602
Well,
now that I got a job,

33:15.645 --> 33:19.562
I figured
I'd start helping out.

33:19.606 --> 33:20.781
You...

33:20.824 --> 33:24.741
you paid for --
for groceries?

33:24.785 --> 33:27.005
Yeah.

33:27.048 --> 33:31.052
Uh, I saw that you were
behind on some bills...

33:31.096 --> 33:35.578
Go on. Go on.
I'm listening.

33:35.622 --> 33:37.319
So, I...

33:37.363 --> 33:39.191
I figured it had a connection
to my school bills,

33:39.234 --> 33:41.236
you -- you know?

33:41.280 --> 33:42.281
And you thought
it was appropriate

33:42.324 --> 33:44.065
to get in my business --

33:44.109 --> 33:49.723
then take it upon yourself
to "help me out"?

33:49.766 --> 33:53.596
Pops, it was just, y-you know,
buying groceries.

33:53.640 --> 33:54.815
That what you thought?

33:54.858 --> 33:56.121
No.
It's not what I --

33:56.164 --> 33:57.644
-Hmm?
-No, not "you" -- "us."

33:57.687 --> 34:00.081
I figured I'd help usout.

34:00.125 --> 34:01.996
Go through my bills?

34:02.040 --> 34:03.389
[ Egg slams ]

34:03.432 --> 34:04.390
Pops!

34:04.433 --> 34:06.435
[ Scoffs ]
Go through my bills.

34:11.527 --> 34:14.182
Buy groceries for my table?

34:14.226 --> 34:15.314
Wow!

34:15.357 --> 34:18.621
[ Scoffs ]

34:18.665 --> 34:20.101
[ Scoffs ]

34:20.145 --> 34:24.540
[ Egg slams ]When I'm in an old age home,

34:24.584 --> 34:29.589
and you got a nice job
making six figures --

34:29.632 --> 34:32.853
when you buy a car
that you pay the insurance on...

34:37.336 --> 34:40.078
...when you have kids
of your own,

34:40.121 --> 34:43.298
then you can pay for all
the groceries you want.

34:43.342 --> 34:48.651
But for now, your job
is to go to school.

34:48.695 --> 34:51.654
Buying food -- that's my job.

34:51.698 --> 34:55.571
And you don't take
another man's job.

34:55.615 --> 34:57.921
Are we clear?

35:03.188 --> 35:05.190
Return the rest of this shit,
and get your money back.

35:11.109 --> 35:16.026
Shut the door,
have a seat.

35:16.070 --> 35:16.897
Fuck's he doing here?

35:16.940 --> 35:18.594
Doctor Babineau tells me

35:18.638 --> 35:22.163
you were planning on sending
Brady Hartsfield off to hospice.

35:22.207 --> 35:23.382
Why is that suddenly
a problem?

35:23.425 --> 35:24.774
You wanted that to happen
from jump.

35:24.818 --> 35:26.254
I hear the patient's
moving his hands,

35:26.298 --> 35:29.083
communicating with
the help of a keyboard.

35:29.127 --> 35:31.259
I honestly believe he'll be
talking in no time, sir.

35:31.303 --> 35:32.521
Look, I don't know what the fuck
this guy's told you,

35:32.565 --> 35:33.827
but it's a bunch
of bullshit.

35:33.870 --> 35:36.438
This town went through
trauma last year --

35:36.482 --> 35:41.400
real trauma --
and now it needs "closure."

35:41.443 --> 35:42.923
Christ.
How many episodes of "Dr. Phil"

35:42.966 --> 35:45.404
do you have on your DVR?

35:45.447 --> 35:47.710
I never believed Hartsfield
would be healthy enough

35:47.754 --> 35:50.844
to stand trail and give
this town what it needs.

35:50.887 --> 35:55.805
But now we might be able
to give the devil his due.

35:55.849 --> 35:57.372
From what Doctor Babineau's
been telling me,

35:57.416 --> 35:59.940
it's looking like
a real possibility.

35:59.983 --> 36:04.684
I think I'll even
try the case myself.

36:04.727 --> 36:07.991
There's a lot going on in that
hospital you don't know about.

36:08.035 --> 36:10.603
Mm, I have
plausible deniability.

36:10.646 --> 36:13.954
You?

36:13.997 --> 36:15.521
You're fucking incredible.

36:15.564 --> 36:20.178
Hartsfield stays --
Have I made myself clear?

36:20.221 --> 36:21.614
Well, that's not up to us,
is it?

36:21.657 --> 36:23.572
I'm aware of that.

36:23.616 --> 36:25.357
Do you know who it is up to?

36:25.400 --> 36:27.707
His name is Neal Jeffries.

36:27.750 --> 36:29.796
He's the CEO of a company
that owns Mercy Gen',

36:29.839 --> 36:32.233
as well as nine other hospitals
in the Midwest.

36:32.277 --> 36:33.800
I don't know him myself.

36:33.843 --> 36:36.629
But I was on his boat
last week.

36:36.672 --> 36:38.892
Who you got on your side?

36:50.947 --> 36:53.385
[ Knocks on door ]

36:58.738 --> 36:59.739
-Hey. Tony.
-Hey, uh --

36:59.782 --> 37:00.914
Hey, can I come in?

37:00.957 --> 37:02.568
Yeah, yeah.
Um...

37:02.611 --> 37:03.569
Don't -- don't get up.

37:03.612 --> 37:07.529
I'm only gonna be here
a second.

37:07.573 --> 37:09.227
Brady's staying.

37:09.270 --> 37:10.445
What?

37:10.489 --> 37:12.969
Lie down, lie down.
Don't -- don't get up.

37:13.013 --> 37:15.276
Babineau got to my boss
the same way he got to me --

37:15.320 --> 37:16.843
he painted a picture
of Hartsfield

37:16.886 --> 37:20.194
being judged for his crimes
in the trail of the century.

37:20.238 --> 37:21.935
Apparently, he moved
his hand yesterday.

37:21.978 --> 37:25.939
-What?
-A-Apparently?

37:25.982 --> 37:30.073
The resurrection's begun.

37:30.117 --> 37:33.033
I thought you should hear it
from me.

37:33.076 --> 37:35.122
-Thanks.
-Take care of yourself, okay?

37:35.165 --> 37:38.168
-Thanks, Tony. Thanks.
-I'll keep you posted.

37:39.692 --> 37:42.347
Sorry about that.

37:47.352 --> 37:50.398
Fucking piece of shit.
Fucking mass murderer.

37:50.442 --> 37:51.399
He'll outlive
the whole lot of us.

37:51.443 --> 37:52.357
No, no, don't.

37:52.400 --> 37:54.054
Give it to me.
Give it to me.

37:54.097 --> 37:57.362
[ Grunts ]

37:57.405 --> 38:01.975
If you let it affect you,
he wins.

38:11.593 --> 38:15.075
[ Sighs ]

38:15.118 --> 38:16.555
He's an affront to humanity.

38:16.598 --> 38:18.034
He's got to be stopped.

38:18.078 --> 38:20.298
Not your job anymore.

38:20.341 --> 38:23.475
It's not your job.

38:23.518 --> 38:26.086
[ Sighs ]

38:34.616 --> 38:37.924
[ Gulps ]

38:41.144 --> 38:43.190
Whose is it?

38:47.847 --> 38:50.632
Okay.

39:01.948 --> 39:05.081
I love you.

39:05.125 --> 39:07.736
I love you, too.

39:07.780 --> 39:10.739
I always have,
and I always will.

39:10.783 --> 39:13.568
I-I know it. Look...

39:13.612 --> 39:16.745
I-I'm not trying to --

39:16.789 --> 39:18.965
It's not that
I-I-I don't under--

39:19.008 --> 39:21.054
I know it's...

39:21.097 --> 39:24.057
I know. I know.

39:24.100 --> 39:27.190
[ Vehicles passing ]

39:31.586 --> 39:34.067
[ Sighs ]

39:34.110 --> 39:35.982
Did you ring Allie?

39:36.025 --> 39:37.375
I did.

39:37.418 --> 39:39.725
I did. She's, um --
she's all right.

39:39.768 --> 39:40.813
That's good.

39:40.856 --> 39:43.381
I told her
you're all right.

39:43.424 --> 39:47.733
Good.

39:47.776 --> 39:50.431
Maybe I should just

39:50.475 --> 39:55.697
go up to Seattle
and visit her for a bit.

39:55.741 --> 39:57.438
Okay. Yeah, good.
Yeah.

39:57.482 --> 39:59.092
Yeah. Yeah.

39:59.135 --> 40:01.747
Want me to --
Want me to tell her anything?

40:05.359 --> 40:08.057
Tell her I love her.

40:14.673 --> 40:16.544
[ Sighs ]

40:30.515 --> 40:34.344
Here you go.

40:34.388 --> 40:35.824
It's not every day
you get a hair sample

40:35.868 --> 40:38.479
from a mass murderer.

40:38.523 --> 40:44.093
The origin of the sample
must remain between us, okay?

40:44.137 --> 40:45.225
So, your friend
at the university,

40:45.268 --> 40:47.488
is she still willing
to run the tests?

40:47.532 --> 40:51.274
I mean, sure.

40:51.318 --> 40:55.888
Great. Okay, so here is
a list of drugs

40:55.931 --> 40:58.281
manufactured by a well-known
pharmaceutical company.

40:58.325 --> 41:02.851
Please see if she can find any
traces of those in the sample.

41:02.895 --> 41:05.985
Also any other
foreign-looking compounds.

41:06.028 --> 41:08.901
I want to know about those,
especially --

41:08.944 --> 41:11.164
the sooner the better.

41:11.207 --> 41:12.600
On it.

41:12.644 --> 41:15.255
I'll drop this off
first thing tomorrow.

41:15.298 --> 41:17.910
Thank you.

41:17.953 --> 41:20.086
[ Birds chirping ]

41:28.094 --> 41:32.794
So, that chemist
is doing you a big favor.

41:32.838 --> 41:35.536
Yeah.

41:35.580 --> 41:38.060
Is she your friend?

41:38.104 --> 41:41.760
Yeah, you could say that.

41:41.803 --> 41:45.415
Is she a close friend?

41:45.459 --> 41:47.983
I guess so.

41:48.027 --> 41:50.638
Is she your girlfriend?

41:50.682 --> 41:52.074
Oh.

41:52.118 --> 41:56.035
N-No. She's not.

41:56.078 --> 41:59.255
Good.

41:59.299 --> 42:00.779
So, once you get
the results back,

42:00.822 --> 42:05.914
I will allow you to take me out
to dinner to discuss them.

42:05.958 --> 42:08.787
Like, a date?

42:08.830 --> 42:11.485
Is that a yes?

42:11.529 --> 42:13.313
Good.

42:13.356 --> 42:16.577
I'll see you then.

42:16.621 --> 42:19.972
Okay.

